TEA was evaluated with total capital investment (TCI) and total production cost (TPC). The total capital investment was estimated by installed costs of all equipment. Herein, the installed cost of the cryogenic system was calculated by the “six-tenths rule” based on previous works, as Eq. (6)43. While the installed costs of other equipment was estimated based on the calculated flowrates and the experimental information, such as acidity and the employed residence times with the Aspen Process Economic Analyzer. All capital investment of the equipment was adjusted to 2018 CNY with location factor of 0.6144 and Chemical Engineering Plant Cost Index (CEPCI)45.6C2C1=S2S10.6\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
